  <discussion>The soft, tart, bright red berries of Vaccinium scoparium, to 6 mm diameter, have fair to good flavor and were gathered and eaten raw by the Kootenay, Okanogan, Shuswap, and other Indian tribes.  Harvesting was probably done using wooden or fish-bone combs.  Small fruit size, low yields, and difficult harvesting make commercial prospects for V. scoparium questionable.</discussion>
